					  <p><h4>Objectives:</h4>
					  <ul type="disc">
					  <li>Consolidate the marketing and promotion material disseminated to members of IPRA so that postal mail and electronic email do not become a burden to its members and a consistent message is being conveyed. 
</li><br>
<li>Adopt an e-Newsletter format, HTML, that will not violate <a href="http://www.spamlaws.com" target="_blank">anti-SPAM laws</a>. </li></ul></p>
<p><h4>Purpose of e-Newsletter:</h4>
<p><ul type="disc"><li>Maintain a professional newsletter that aims to educate the park and recreation professional members of IPRA. 
</li><br>
<li>The monthly e-Newsletter is not an open forum for posting park district events. Rather, the e-Newsletter shall have two main sections: "Upcoming Events" and a section for general news that members will find beneficial to their professional development.</li></ul><br></p>
<p><h4>Requesting of Information to be Posted:</h4>
<p><ul type="disc"><li>Each month IPRA sections will have the opportunity to submit events, educational seminars, etc. to the e-Newsletter.</li><br>
<li>Information will be posted on a first-come, first-serve basis following strict content guidelines.</li><br>
<li>All information will be subject to approval by IRPA staff.</li><br>
<li>The <a href="/resources/newsletterform.cfm">e-Newsletter Request Form</a> shall be completed and submitted by the first of the month to be considered for the next month’s e-Newsletter. (example: submit information by April 1, 2005 for May e-Newsletter)</li></ul><br></p>	

